items.name: Dragonborn Concept LoRA
items.description:
Dragonborn concept LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

  • Comparison with all the variants 🐲 https://civitai.com/posts/419495

  • Creative uses: https://civitai.com/posts/424514

Trained on DreamShaper 7, triggers with dragonborn, plus other tokens (see examples), optionally wings, bat wings, dragon wings for level 14 ones. You can also decide the chromatic or metallic variant just by prompting the subtype, such as red dragonborn or silver dragonborn. Again see the examples (I added pink just for fun and because I had many pink examples in the dataset for some reason and I didn't want the base one default to pink).

Should work on basically any model and any style, but I tested it on AAM, AnyLoRA, DreamShaper and AbsoluteReality.

I had a lot of fun using it. Should work around weight 1.

Some examples are too "sexy". You need to register to see them.


How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.description:
Lora trained on Soul Fighter Evelynn from League of Legends

requested by: @themangamer123

tags: soul fighter evelynn, 1girl, cropped jacket, hat, pants, short hair, blonde hair, cleavage, purple lips

anime: Kawaii Realistic Anime Mix - A0.2, YabaL_Mix - V5, Cetus-Mix

2,5D: Aniverse - Aniverse V1.1, Dark Sushi 2.5D, MeinaUnreal - V4.1, DarkSun - v4.0

realistic: Paragon V1.0, Kawaii Realistic European Mix - v0.3

negative embeddings: Fast Negative Embedding v2

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realistic models & 2,5D), kl-f8-anime2, blessed2.vae (for anime models)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras(euler a for img2img upscaling) from time to time im also using DPM++ 2M alt Karras

  • Steps: 20 to 35

  • Clipskip: 2

  • Upscaler : GitHub - pkuliyi2015/multidiffusion-upscaler-for-automatic1111 4x-UltraSharp(for 2,5D & realistic), 4xAnimesharp(for anime)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9 (mostly 7)

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.8 and 1)

  • Denoise strength upscaling: 0.3 to 0.55

If you want to autocomplete the tags & trigger im using, I recommend using Booru style tag autocompletion for AUTOMATIC1111's Stable Diffusion web UI

For full body shots i recommend using: ComfyUI Impact Pack

or the a1111 alternative GitHub - Bing-su/adetailer

items.name: Androids & mechanical parts concept
items.description:
This is a concept lycoris for android, humanoid robots and mechanical parts (arms, legs) that won't bleed too much art style into your images. If you plan to use it together with character or style loras, it will be perfect for that!

Trained with LoKr for easy portability and reduced style and unintended concept bleeding.

How to use

Use "android" and any other trigger word in your prompts. Increase the weight of the "android" token and reduce the one that can interfere with the mechanical traits from an android or robot (nude, completely nude, etc.).

For instance:

masterpiece, best quality, highest quality, highly detailed,
beautiful, intricate details, absurdres,

1girl, solo, android, robot, mechanical parts, mechanical arms,
indigo hair, medium hair, chignon,
starry print eyes, :o,
nude,
gigantic breasts,

BREAK

from behind, outdoors, cityscape, sunset, post-apocalypse, science fiction,

BREAK

looking away,

BREAK

<lora:droids_LoKr_prodigy_v1-01-000017:1>

Development notes:

The training images were tagged using conv2, swinv2 and moat at the same time and then merged together and the duplicate tags removed.


No revised captions, signature/watermark/censorship removal for now, but I will start doing it in the next batches.

Additional data prep was done to remove edges and artifacts from the downscaled images.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. items.description:
My rating vs expectation: 96%

(High quality dataset. High level of likeness and was trained the best way I knew how. Unlikely to see more improvement from me.)

All TIs I make depict real adults. Please apply it with good judgement. If you're the model and want this removed reach out to me via link below. I welcome all criticisms and suggestions with curiosity. If you like my work, buy me a house:
https://ko-fi.com/futurafree

This is probably my favorite TI to date. I definitely took my time with this one and the result is stunning. There is virtually no detectable difference imo. The capability of TI in subject learning is quite incredible. I'm curious to hear what you think.

This TI was trained in sd1.5 base with 5 vectors, 45 images, 14120 steps, and 314 epochs. This was finetuned for epiCRealism evo3 and Realistic Vision V4.0, but may work on others.

TIPS:

  • MUST be the first word in the prompt for likeness and consistency.

    • Example: futuraalice14120v5, portrait of a woman, long dress etc.

    • Not: Portrait of futuraalice14120v5, etc.

  • Recommended strength:

    • (0.98-1.0)

  • I use adetailer for all images, with mediapipe_face_full, blank pos and neg, 1024x1024, inpaint mask blur: 20, inpaint noise strength: 0.45.

  • Again, prompt in adetailer is left blank most of the time; (*exception*: if Loras/Lycoris is used and has significant impact on the appearance of the model's face, copy paste pos prompt without Loras/Lycoris into adetailer).

  • Upscaler I use: 4x_NMKD-Siax_200k.

items.name: Grunge style interior design
items.description:
Only for SD 2.1

Grunge style interior design embodies the raw, edgy, and rebellious aesthetic of the grunge movement that originated in the music scene of the 1980s and 90s. It's characterized by a distressed, worn-out look, often with a touch of industrial elements.

The color palette is usually dark and moody, featuring tones like black, charcoal, deep red, and forest green. The use of unfinished, weathered, or reclaimed materials, such as wood and metal, is a common trait.

Furniture in grunge design tends to be vintage or industrial-looking, with plenty of worn leather, rusted metal, and distressed wood. The style encourages a mix-and-match approach, often combining pieces from different eras and styles.

Decorative elements typically have a worn, faded look, contributing to an atmosphere of comfortable disarray. This could include faded band posters, vintage rugs, old books, or antique lamps. Walls can be adorned with murals, graffiti, or peeling wallpaper to enhance the grunge aesthetic.

In essence, grunge style interior design is about authenticity and individuality. It's a style that embraces the imperfect, the worn, and the casually thrown together, creating spaces that feel lived-in, relaxed, and effortlessly cool.

modelVersions.name: v1.0
modelVersions.description:
initial version

I do like the results (finally), but it took a few attempts. I thought I had great training images/text, but the first couple batches were really bad. I'm using decent sized training images (1024x1024) and the push to have 5 epochs seems to be working ok. However, I find pumping up the denoising on the upscaler really helped. Pretty much all of the checkpoints responded well to that.

The other issue that is still present in the model is one related to my personal preference for banshees. I tend to insert the token white cloak for all of the banshees, as the model will produce dark cloaked subjects if it isn't present - and I really wanted it to be a bit more ghostly. skeletal is another token worth including in most.

The images were created with hires.fx x2, denoising 0.7, 4x_foolhardy_Remacri upscaler

items.name: Jubilee (X-Men) LoRA
items.description:
A LoRA for everyone's favorite young mutant girl, Kitty Pryde -- cough -- Jubilee!

Info

  • Activation Tag is "jubilee," best used at 0.6 - 1 strength.

  • Includes her 90s outfit ("crop top, raincoat, jean shorts, eyewear on head") which is the default that will usually generate with her if you don't prompt anything and her more modern look ("black bodysuit, raincoat, eyewear on head").

  • The recent X-terminators look ("oversized clothes, oversized shirt, thigh highs, garter straps") is also in here because I thought it was cute. It's rare though since data is scarce.

  • Also trained on her vampire form a bit so fangs should be easy if you want them.

  • "Sparkles" , "Fireworks" , "balls of light" , "Magic" , etc can all be used to generate objects similar to her mutant power.

Issues

  • The eyewear can bleed into the hair, dye the hair, or generate both on her head and on her face (more of an issue for realistic models).

  • The shirt may generate yellow.

  • She likes to wave her hands when no pose is prompted.

  • If you add her gloves, they might glow due to data including her mutant power in use.

  • May generate a small ponytail/bun, especially when using "from behind" as the AI confuses the eyewear for a hairtie sometimes.

  • When generating her vampire fangs, the AI LOVES to add batwings.

This Lora was made purely for a fun and self-learning experiences. I DID NOT INTEND and DO NOT give permissions for this LoRA to be used for any commercial/promotional/financial gain uses.
